{
  "stem": "11274.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Did I tell you first that I was-- shared the Hebrew lessons with my sister Danka when I came home from the Hebrew school?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I shared lessons-- she knew it-- she was-- knew all the lessons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she could read it and write it, too-- the Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not the German.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't share.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The German have two alphabets, they have the Gothic alphabet and the regular.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So it was a little bit difficult for me to bring it home and share it with her.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was a two year older sister, and the oldest sister was 14 years older-- already married and had her children.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I was the guardian of my youngest sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], watch out for the little one-- was always-- and I took it seriously later on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The rest of my life, I took care of the little one whenever it was necessary.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But during to school-- during the year that I was going for extended education in the summers, we needed some pocket money.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were living from the farm, mainly, with enough food and everything else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But there were some things that a young girl-- excuse me-- wants to buy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Dad said, it's OK, so long as it is somewhere-- you had to stay there if you want a nanny to a Jewish family's child because they wanted you to stay in the room with the child, if they had one child.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And for my father, he had to check first if it was a kosher restaurant.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a kosher hotel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "If it was a kosher hotel, the restaurant-- he approved of everything-- that it was OK.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I had-- for two summers-- a little four-year, and then five-year-old boy there.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
